Extremely outdated source which cites an even older source by an Islamic scholar. The Yazidis mentioned in his book were likely not the same as these ones. This Unaisa figure seems to have had good relations with the Ibadi sect who are located in Southern Arabia, nowhere near the Yezidi community of Kurdistan. In addition, the coincidence of the names are not unusual. There's been other sects and dynasties named Yazidi.
